title: NED (2003) Comedy
description:
Ned (2003) is an Australian film, directed by Abe Forsythe. It is satire of Australian outlaw Ned Kelly, and his iconographical status as a "hero."

In November 2006 on Vega FM host Shaun Micallef called Ned "The funniest Australian film made in the last ten years."

Good copies of this movie are very rare. There are 2 DVDs of this movie on ebay at the moment and the cheapest is $75, the other one is $100. 

The other copy on TPB is not too bad, but it was ripped at the wrong frame rate causing a skip/pausing action, and the audio went out of sync about 30 mins in, but my thanks to the uploader for that upload, as it tied me over till I got a hold of a full DVD version to rip.
